WEBVTT

00:00.031 --> 00:01.382
<i>Previously on "Dark Matter"...</i>

00:01.413 --> 00:04.671
<i>- Are you saying Sarah's alive?
- When her stasis pod died,</i>

00:04.718 --> 00:07.548
<i>I was able to rescue her
digital consciousness.</i>

00:07.583 --> 00:10.484
You can neurally connect to her world.

00:10.515 --> 00:13.354
- You're not Tabor.
- Oh, right, the amnesia thing.

00:13.389 --> 00:15.923
Tabor told me. Adrian Maro,
Tabor's former assistant.

00:15.958 --> 00:17.391
We were kinda hoping maybe we could stay

00:17.393 --> 00:19.293
with you guys for a while.

00:19.328 --> 00:20.807
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:20.823 --> 00:23.263
- [grunts]
<i>- The needle was poisoned.</i>

00:23.298 --> 00:25.976
<i>Round up his family and
his closest friends.</i>

00:26.016 --> 00:28.936
Guilty or not, an example must be made.

00:29.905 --> 00:34.375
[wind whistling]

00:34.410 --> 00:37.378
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:37.413 --> 00:41.348
<i>♪</i>

00:41.383 --> 00:44.023
I want two dozen
prisoners to a cargo hold.

00:44.053 --> 00:45.853
No more, no less.

00:45.888 --> 00:47.621
Let's go.

00:47.656 --> 00:50.290
Move.

00:50.325 --> 00:54.228
<i>♪</i>

00:54.263 --> 00:56.397
Come on.

00:56.432 --> 00:58.132
Move. Let's go.

00:58.174 --> 01:05.180
<i>♪</i>

01:07.078 --> 01:10.310
The journey to Inari-7 should
take less than 48 hours.

01:10.633 --> 01:12.279
In this time, you'll be questioned

01:12.314 --> 01:15.282
regarding any anti-imperial
acts you may have witnessed

01:15.317 --> 01:16.917
or any suspicions you may have

01:16.952 --> 01:19.420
regarding neighbors'
or friends' loyalty.

01:19.455 --> 01:20.888
We're loyal to Emperor Ishida!

01:20.923 --> 01:22.589
Our people have proudly served

01:22.624 --> 01:24.258
the royal court for generations.

01:24.293 --> 01:25.793
And yet one of your fellow clansmen

01:25.828 --> 01:27.670
plotted to kill our beloved emperor.

01:27.694 --> 01:29.163
None of us had prior knowledge

01:29.198 --> 01:30.698
of his intentions.

01:30.733 --> 01:32.099
We'll see about that.

01:32.134 --> 01:35.269
You have no right to keep us here.

01:35.304 --> 01:37.104
We're following the emperor's orders.

01:37.139 --> 01:39.673
Are you questioning his
right to rule over you?

01:39.708 --> 01:43.610
I question a ruler who would
deny his subjects their freedom

01:43.645 --> 01:48.549
on the basis of unfounded
suspicion and fear!

01:48.584 --> 01:50.651
I accept your confession of treason.

01:52.187 --> 01:53.520
<i>♪</i>

01:53.555 --> 01:55.956
No. No, no, no, no.

01:55.991 --> 01:57.491
No!

01:57.526 --> 02:00.027
I'm loyal to the emperor!

02:00.062 --> 02:03.530
No! Please!

02:03.565 --> 02:05.199
Would anyone else like to question

02:05.234 --> 02:08.335
the royal court's
decision in this matter?

02:08.370 --> 02:15.376
<i>♪</i>

02:17.346 --> 02:20.314
[people murmuring]

02:20.349 --> 02:27.388
<i>♪</i>

02:30.025 --> 02:34.115
<i>[rock music]</i>

02:34.154 --> 02:40.118
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

02:43.539 --> 02:44.538
[cot clanging]

02:44.573 --> 02:46.707
[snorts]

02:46.742 --> 02:49.010
Glad to see you're
taking this seriously.

02:51.313 --> 02:53.947
For your information, I was
only pretending to sleep.

02:53.982 --> 02:55.282
Hmm.

02:55.317 --> 02:56.817
It's much easier to eavesdrop

02:56.852 --> 02:58.318
when no one knows you're listening.

02:58.353 --> 03:00.754
Right, so the snoring was just for show?

03:00.789 --> 03:01.789
I had to convince him.

03:01.824 --> 03:03.524
And the drool?

03:03.559 --> 03:07.094
It's the little details
that make it work.

03:07.129 --> 03:09.263
So what did you learn?

03:09.298 --> 03:11.999
Gideon. He's the one in charge.

03:12.034 --> 03:14.234
Think we can convince him?

03:14.269 --> 03:16.132
What, you worried all this ain't enough?

03:17.239 --> 03:19.406
[sighs]

03:19.441 --> 03:22.443
[indistinct chatter]

03:26.548 --> 03:28.849
Rumor has it you're the
one in charge here...

03:28.884 --> 03:31.552
Aside from our Ishida captors, that is.

03:31.587 --> 03:35.088
I look after my people as best I can.

03:35.123 --> 03:38.425
And that includes most everyone
we came on board with...

03:38.460 --> 03:40.460
Except you two.

03:40.495 --> 03:42.129
So who are you?

03:42.164 --> 03:44.932
All you need to know is
that we're here to help.

03:44.967 --> 03:46.673
How?

03:46.705 --> 03:48.514
Getting you off this ship, for starters.

03:48.546 --> 03:51.471
That assassination attempt
made the emperor look weak.

03:51.506 --> 03:54.441
Now he's gonna make a big show
of stamping out any disloyalty.

03:54.476 --> 03:56.810
Like it or not, you're
a part of that show.

03:56.845 --> 03:58.812
And by "show," she's talking about

03:58.847 --> 04:00.747
a very public round of executions

04:00.782 --> 04:02.616
just to prove to everyone
he's still in charge.

04:02.618 --> 04:04.384
Even if we could escape,
where would we go?

04:04.419 --> 04:06.420
We got contacts in the Outer Colonies,

04:06.455 --> 04:08.655
the ones that have recently
declared independence.

04:08.690 --> 04:10.157
And they'd help us?

04:10.192 --> 04:11.725
They already agreed to take you in.

04:11.760 --> 04:14.461
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:14.496 --> 04:17.497
It's a new life for you and your people,

04:17.531 --> 04:20.166
one where no one has any power over you.

04:20.202 --> 04:23.136
All you have to do is
seize the opportunity...

04:23.171 --> 04:25.439
By helping us take this ship.

04:25.474 --> 04:29.877
<i>♪</i>

04:32.881 --> 04:35.282
Reports of losses are still coming in,

04:35.317 --> 04:38.085
but it looks like the blockade has held.

04:38.120 --> 04:39.653
Good.

04:39.688 --> 04:41.989
Redirect ships from the Atria sector.

04:42.024 --> 04:44.157
Reinforce our positions
along Chara 2 and 3.

04:44.192 --> 04:47.361
But that may leave Atria
vulnerable to attack.

04:47.396 --> 04:50.230
The planets in that sector
have proven valuable allies.

04:50.265 --> 04:52.766
And their sacrifice will be
recognized if it comes to that.

04:52.801 --> 04:54.334
The blockade is our priority.

04:54.369 --> 04:56.470
Yes, Emperor. I'll see it done.

04:56.505 --> 04:58.472
Thank you, General Ueda.

05:03.445 --> 05:05.479
Teku, what news?

05:05.514 --> 05:09.016
Are we any closer to
identifying the coconspirators?

05:09.051 --> 05:11.451
[sighs] To be frank, Heika,

05:11.486 --> 05:14.554
I don't believe there were any.

05:14.589 --> 05:16.156
[sighs]

05:16.191 --> 05:18.125
We have questioned many of his people,

05:18.160 --> 05:20.260
but none could provide any information

05:20.295 --> 05:21.535
about the attempt on your life.

05:21.563 --> 05:22.930
Well, perhaps the examiners

05:22.965 --> 05:25.499
aren't asking the right questions.

05:25.534 --> 05:28.001
I'd like to announce the
conspirators have been caught

05:28.036 --> 05:30.351
and set a date for their
trial by the end of the week.

05:30.354 --> 05:31.638
But, Emperor...

05:31.673 --> 05:34.041
It is best to move
quickly in these matters

05:34.076 --> 05:36.810
to give the people the
reassurance they deserve.

05:36.845 --> 05:39.112
Don't you agree?

05:39.147 --> 05:41.182
Yes, Emperor.

05:44.186 --> 05:47.221
[breathes deeply]

05:49.091 --> 05:52.560
[indistinct chatter]

05:58.066 --> 05:59.766
We hit them after their next check-in.

05:59.801 --> 06:01.735
That'll give us 20
minutes to take the bridge.

06:01.770 --> 06:03.084
What do you need us to do?

06:03.087 --> 06:05.038
Create a distraction so
we can take out the guards.

06:05.040 --> 06:06.506
Then we'll deal with the rest.

06:06.541 --> 06:08.408
But we can help you take the bridge.

06:08.443 --> 06:11.211
You'll just get in the way...
and probably get killed.

06:11.246 --> 06:12.813
At least let us free our friends

06:12.848 --> 06:14.581
from the other cargo holds.

06:14.616 --> 06:17.384
This needs to go down quick and quiet.

06:17.419 --> 06:19.219
If they discover any of us are missing,

06:19.254 --> 06:21.602
they'll enact a lockdown,
and then we're all screwed.

06:21.605 --> 06:23.224
We'll handle it.

06:24.293 --> 06:25.860
She's going with you.

06:25.895 --> 06:26.993
We just told you...

06:27.016 --> 06:28.595
Look, she's one person.

06:28.630 --> 06:29.730
She won't slow you down.

06:29.765 --> 06:31.431
[scoffs]

06:31.466 --> 06:32.767
Can you fight?

06:32.821 --> 06:35.809
Served for five years
with the planetary guard.

06:35.837 --> 06:39.706
Want a demonstration?

06:39.741 --> 06:41.975
That won't be necessary.

06:42.010 --> 06:44.118
Okay, you're with us.

06:49.351 --> 06:51.618
Might just pull this off.

06:51.653 --> 06:53.754
What, you had doubts?

06:53.789 --> 06:56.156
Never.

06:56.191 --> 06:59.193
[engines whooshing]

07:05.033 --> 07:07.000
Here we go.

07:07.035 --> 07:09.302
Yup.

07:09.337 --> 07:10.937
[both grunting]

07:10.972 --> 07:12.906
Hey!

07:12.941 --> 07:14.474
Hey!

07:14.509 --> 07:18.645
[both grunting]

07:18.680 --> 07:20.213
<i>[radio static crackles]</i>

07:20.248 --> 07:22.249
[grunting]

07:22.284 --> 07:26.553
[both grunting]

07:26.588 --> 07:29.489
<i>[intense music]</i>

07:29.524 --> 07:30.524
Let's go.

07:32.961 --> 07:34.327
Sit tight.

07:34.362 --> 07:41.202
<i>♪</i>

07:42.204 --> 07:43.236
[gunshots]

07:43.271 --> 07:44.237
[grunts]

07:44.272 --> 07:51.278
<i>♪</i>

07:54.749 --> 07:58.485
[gunshots]

07:58.520 --> 08:01.955
[alarm blaring]

08:01.990 --> 08:03.223
Turn that thing off!

08:03.258 --> 08:05.192
Relax, sweetheart.

08:05.227 --> 08:06.993
Hard part's over.

08:07.028 --> 08:11.565
[blaring continues]

08:11.600 --> 08:14.167
[mechanical whirring]

08:14.202 --> 08:17.671
Okay, I've got full control
of the ship's systems,

08:17.706 --> 08:20.373
and I've just locked down
the interior corridors.

08:20.408 --> 08:21.942
Now free the prisoners.

08:21.977 --> 08:23.376
Yup, you got it.

08:23.411 --> 08:25.479
<i>[beeping]</i>

08:25.514 --> 08:28.516
[blaring continues]

08:32.654 --> 08:33.854
Oh, my God.

08:33.889 --> 08:35.054
They're opening the air lock!

08:35.090 --> 08:37.090
[whirring]

08:37.125 --> 08:39.359
[people yelling]

08:39.394 --> 08:41.561
<i>[beeping]</i>

08:41.596 --> 08:43.263
What are you doing?

08:43.298 --> 08:44.588
Cleaning house.

08:44.631 --> 08:46.531
<i>♪</i>

08:46.574 --> 08:48.142
[gunshot]

08:54.751 --> 08:56.775
<i>Commander Truffault, you are receiving</i>

08:56.821 --> 08:59.948
<i>a subspace transmission
from an unauthorized source.</i>

08:59.983 --> 09:02.284
Has the sender identified themselves?

09:02.319 --> 09:03.346
<i>Yes, Commander.</i>

09:03.385 --> 09:07.456
<i>They claim to be the crew of the "Raza."</i>

09:07.491 --> 09:09.358
Put them through.

09:11.462 --> 09:14.797
Hello, Commander. How goes the war?

09:14.832 --> 09:17.533
The Mikkei Combine has
managed to stay out of it.

09:17.568 --> 09:18.834
How long will that last?

09:18.869 --> 09:20.936
Well, hopefully until the end

09:20.971 --> 09:22.938
of this unfortunate conflict.

09:22.973 --> 09:25.541
At which point Mikkei will
step into the power vacuum

09:25.576 --> 09:27.609
unscathed and resource rich?

09:27.644 --> 09:29.614
<i>You really think Ferrous
is gonna let that happen?</i>

09:29.617 --> 09:31.880
I'm not sure they'll
have much of a choice.

09:31.915 --> 09:34.550
Their hands are rather full.

09:36.253 --> 09:37.786
Now, either you've redecorated,

09:37.821 --> 09:39.622
or you've found yourselves a new ship.

09:40.744 --> 09:42.311
Yes.

09:42.339 --> 09:44.660
We have doubled the size of our fleet.

09:44.695 --> 09:45.800
<i>I'm surprised.</i>

09:45.824 --> 09:47.494
<i>I thought you and Emperor Ishida</i>

09:47.497 --> 09:48.864
<i>weren't on the best of terms.</i>

09:48.866 --> 09:50.265
Oh, we aren't.

09:50.300 --> 09:51.900
This cruiser isn't so much lent

09:51.935 --> 09:53.475
as it is liberated.

09:53.514 --> 09:55.471
<i>Stealing warships...</i>

09:55.506 --> 09:56.944
<i>My, you've upped your game.</i>

09:56.947 --> 09:58.807
This ship does have a lot of firepower,

09:58.842 --> 10:00.642
but that's not why we took it.

10:00.677 --> 10:02.578
Zairon's at war with Pyr,

10:02.613 --> 10:04.880
but in the bigger corporate conflict,

10:04.915 --> 10:06.215
they're officially neutral.

10:06.250 --> 10:07.716
Allowing a ship like that

10:07.751 --> 10:09.751
free passage through contested areas.

10:09.786 --> 10:11.553
<i>No one will be looking too closely at us</i>

10:11.588 --> 10:13.589
<i>or anything we might be transporting.</i>

10:13.624 --> 10:14.890
That could be useful,

10:14.925 --> 10:16.525
if you're looking to move cargo

10:16.560 --> 10:18.393
that requires a bit of extra discretion.

10:18.428 --> 10:20.396
Know anyone like that?

10:22.966 --> 10:24.367
I'll be in touch.

10:26.270 --> 10:30.305
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:30.340 --> 10:31.440
Hmm.

10:31.475 --> 10:33.509
All right.

10:33.544 --> 10:34.576
We're in business.

10:34.611 --> 10:36.278
Mm-hmm.

10:36.313 --> 10:38.580
You know, we make a pretty good team.

10:38.615 --> 10:40.015
- Oh?
- Yeah.

10:40.050 --> 10:41.116
Ugh.

10:41.151 --> 10:44.219
Oh. I like this.

10:44.254 --> 10:46.488
It's got kind of an "all
hail our glorious leader"

10:46.523 --> 10:48.056
sort of vibe to it.

10:48.091 --> 10:49.858
Android, any progress

10:49.893 --> 10:50.993
establishing a neural link?

10:51.028 --> 10:52.161
Not yet.

10:52.196 --> 10:53.196
As I stated earlier,

10:53.259 --> 10:55.164
connection is theoretically possible,

10:55.199 --> 10:56.565
but such a function was not part

10:56.600 --> 10:58.200
of this ship's original design.

10:58.235 --> 11:00.903
What's with the no-can-do attitude?

11:00.938 --> 11:02.638
That wasn't pessimism,

11:02.673 --> 11:04.206
simply a statement of fact,

11:04.241 --> 11:06.108
like, "We stole a ship,"

11:06.143 --> 11:08.010
"We're flying through space,"

11:08.045 --> 11:10.846
or, "I could detach your
head with minimal effort."

11:10.881 --> 11:12.314
- Okay.
- Minimal...

11:12.349 --> 11:13.749
- Yeah. Okay.
- Effort.

11:13.784 --> 11:15.017
I got it.

11:15.052 --> 11:17.052
Testy robot.

11:17.087 --> 11:18.620
So how'd it go with Truffault?

11:18.655 --> 11:21.023
- She buy it?
- Yeah, I think so.

11:21.058 --> 11:22.791
Still can't believe we're
gonna work with that bitch.

11:22.793 --> 11:23.925
She hates us.

11:23.928 --> 11:25.427
Not in this universe, she doesn't.

11:25.429 --> 11:26.695
You should have seen them,

11:26.730 --> 11:28.386
yakking on like old friends.

11:28.410 --> 11:30.999
Yeah, old friends until
we double-cross her.

11:31.034 --> 11:33.669
Incoming transmission.

11:34.671 --> 11:36.706
- Get out.
- All right.

11:38.141 --> 11:40.576
<i>[beeping]</i>

11:40.611 --> 11:41.910
<i>Two. [sighs]</i>

11:41.945 --> 11:43.378
<i>I should've known.</i>

11:43.413 --> 11:46.081
Hello, Emperor. What can I do for you?

11:46.116 --> 11:48.083
<i>I want my ship back, for starters.</i>

11:48.118 --> 11:52.087
Oh, sorry, but we have plans
for this sweet, sweet ride.

11:52.122 --> 11:53.956
<i>You stole the Blink Drive from me,</i>

11:53.991 --> 11:55.991
<i>destroyed a research facility</i>

11:56.026 --> 11:58.425
<i>that set my war efforts back years,</i>

11:58.428 --> 12:00.028
<i>and now you take one of my ships?</i>

12:00.063 --> 12:01.964
Too ambitious?

12:01.999 --> 12:04.333
<i>I know you still blame me
for what happened to Nyx,</i>

12:04.368 --> 12:06.368
<i>and even though she
didn't die by my own hand,</i>

12:06.403 --> 12:08.270
<i>I still bear the guilt of her death.</i>

12:08.305 --> 12:09.739
<i>And I accept...</i>

12:10.974 --> 12:12.674
[laughs]

12:12.709 --> 12:15.110
You know, I miss that kid's moxie.

12:15.145 --> 12:17.713
<i>[static crackling]</i>

12:19.249 --> 12:20.650
[sighs]

12:22.386 --> 12:24.886
I caution restraint.

12:24.921 --> 12:26.588
They want to provoke me?

12:26.623 --> 12:29.091
I will bring the full force
of Zairon down on them.

12:29.126 --> 12:30.826
The full force of Zairon

12:30.861 --> 12:33.762
is presently engaged in
more pressing matters.

12:33.797 --> 12:37.399
It is unwise to commit
valuable resources

12:37.434 --> 12:38.767
to a personal vendetta.

12:38.802 --> 12:40.168
They targeted me,

12:40.203 --> 12:42.171
and I will respond with force!

12:47.444 --> 12:49.378
They attacked the house of Ishida.

12:49.413 --> 12:50.979
They stole from us.

12:51.014 --> 12:53.949
It is my duty as the emperor to respond.

12:55.686 --> 12:57.319
Forgive me, Emperor.

12:57.354 --> 13:01.189
I did not mean to offend.

13:01.224 --> 13:02.824
And you haven't.

13:02.859 --> 13:06.094
Your counsel is always welcome, Teku...

13:06.129 --> 13:09.798
no matter how idealized and misdirected.

13:09.833 --> 13:11.767
Move!

13:18.823 --> 13:20.857
<i>The Mikkei shuttle has docked.</i>

13:20.900 --> 13:21.866
Good.

13:21.893 --> 13:22.973
Seal off all doors

13:22.989 --> 13:24.786
between the cargo hold and the air lock.

13:24.825 --> 13:26.481
We wouldn't want anyone wandering.

13:26.516 --> 13:28.384
<i>Yes, Portia.</i>

13:29.553 --> 13:31.219
Whoa, hey.

13:31.254 --> 13:33.889
Remember, we are
supposed to be friendly.

13:33.924 --> 13:35.657
Put it away.

13:35.669 --> 13:38.037
[door clanking and hissing]

13:38.095 --> 13:39.962
This way, grunts.

13:41.431 --> 13:43.765
Truffault said you'd have
information about the drop.

13:43.800 --> 13:45.267
Here you go.

13:50.173 --> 13:53.408
This planet is in Traugott territory.

13:53.443 --> 13:54.576
That a problem?

13:54.611 --> 13:57.279
Not for us.

13:57.314 --> 13:59.414
No information about the
cargo we're hauling for you?

13:59.416 --> 14:01.583
The less you know, the better.

14:01.618 --> 14:03.552
Careful, you clumsy idiots!

14:03.587 --> 14:06.889
Do you want to get us all killed?

14:08.191 --> 14:10.759
Please at least attempt
to follow the protocol.

14:10.794 --> 14:12.795
All right.

14:16.199 --> 14:18.834
Half now, the other half on delivery.

14:18.869 --> 14:21.203
Yeah, we are all good.

14:21.238 --> 14:22.704
Who wants?

14:22.739 --> 14:24.606
Mm!

14:24.641 --> 14:25.607
[sniffs]

14:25.642 --> 14:27.209
We done?

14:27.244 --> 14:28.543
Yes.

14:28.578 --> 14:30.345
All right. Let's go.

14:30.380 --> 14:34.650
Tash, see these men
safely back to their ship.

14:39.556 --> 14:41.423
The hell you doing with that?

14:41.458 --> 14:44.426
What, I can't be curious about
the planet we're not visiting?

14:44.461 --> 14:46.262
[sighs]

14:47.798 --> 14:50.800
[engines rumbling]

14:55.172 --> 14:58.174
<i>[whirring and beeping]</i>

15:03.714 --> 15:06.448
Still no success in reaching Six?

15:06.483 --> 15:09.551
It's been days since we last talked.

15:09.586 --> 15:12.621
I assume he must be busy.

15:12.656 --> 15:16.191
Too busy to call just
to say he's too busy?

15:16.226 --> 15:18.960
Too busy to even accept
my comm transmission?

15:18.995 --> 15:20.629
He did make it clear

15:20.664 --> 15:22.898
that his new duties
on the outer colonies

15:22.933 --> 15:24.966
would command a great
deal of his attention

15:25.001 --> 15:26.968
and that he wouldn't
be as available to you

15:27.003 --> 15:28.303
as he was in the past.

15:28.338 --> 15:30.672
Yeah. I know.

15:30.707 --> 15:34.543
But that doesn't mean
he isn't missing you too.

15:34.578 --> 15:36.111
<i>[pinging]</i>

15:36.146 --> 15:37.947
Maybe that's him now.

15:41.651 --> 15:43.084
Commander Truffault.

15:43.119 --> 15:45.687
What the hell is your crew playing at?

15:45.722 --> 15:48.690
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:48.725 --> 15:50.926
<i>♪</i>

15:50.961 --> 15:52.694
[engines rumbling]

15:52.729 --> 15:54.344
<i>I'm telling you, we haven't stolen</i>

15:54.375 --> 15:57.132
an Ishida cruiser or taken
delivery of any missiles.

15:57.167 --> 16:00.302
<i>And I suppose you're gonna
deny contacting me as well?</i>

16:00.337 --> 16:01.903
- Yes.
<i>- Oh, seriously,</i>

16:01.938 --> 16:03.805
<i>that's the best you can come up with?</i>

16:03.840 --> 16:05.574
Look, I don't know what's going on,

16:05.609 --> 16:08.710
but I assure you we had
nothing to do with it.

16:08.745 --> 16:12.047
<i>Pending the return of those
missiles and the cash,</i>

16:12.082 --> 16:16.151
<i>consider our unlikely
alliance suspended.</i>

16:19.389 --> 16:23.025
Well... that was weird.

16:25.902 --> 16:28.670
[engines rumbling]

16:32.202 --> 16:34.035
- Hey.
- Hey.

16:34.070 --> 16:36.371
You figure out why Truffault
thinks we double-crossed her?

16:36.373 --> 16:38.540
Yeah. Because we did double-cross her.

16:38.575 --> 16:40.675
Damn. I must be getting old.

16:40.710 --> 16:42.570
My memory is not what it used to be.

16:42.609 --> 16:44.712
I had The Android access
the GA general database

16:44.714 --> 16:46.681
and search for any
official sightings of us

16:46.716 --> 16:48.049
over the last few months.

16:48.084 --> 16:50.652
Check it out.

16:50.687 --> 16:53.288
Month and a half ago, Rigel-9.

16:53.323 --> 16:56.391
- Three weeks ago, Kleeia-3.
- Cool.

16:56.426 --> 17:00.095
Except I've never been
to Rigel-9 or Kleeia-3.

17:01.231 --> 17:03.465
Tash and Wexler.

17:03.500 --> 17:06.034
Hmm?

17:06.069 --> 17:08.303
Well, guess we now know
who took that ride back

17:08.338 --> 17:09.714
from the alternate universe, huh?

17:09.722 --> 17:11.539
Well, we can't just let them fly around,

17:11.540 --> 17:12.874
trashing your reputations.

17:12.909 --> 17:14.843
To be fair, kid,

17:14.877 --> 17:16.578
our reputations are
already pretty trashed.

17:16.613 --> 17:17.698
No, she's right.

17:17.730 --> 17:19.247
We can't let them get away with this.

17:19.249 --> 17:20.882
So what are we gonna do?

17:20.916 --> 17:23.385
Well, first we're gonna find them,

17:23.420 --> 17:25.421
and then we're gonna deal with them.

17:27.069 --> 17:30.464
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:30.499 --> 17:33.033
<i>♪</i>

17:34.623 --> 17:36.423
Hey.

17:36.458 --> 17:37.958
What do you got there?

17:37.993 --> 17:40.260
First present Tabor ever gave me.

17:40.295 --> 17:43.897
It's an antique he won in
a poker game on Artemis-9.

17:43.932 --> 17:45.632
Really makes you realize...

17:45.667 --> 17:47.901
How much you miss him?

17:47.936 --> 17:49.272
No, what a jerk he was.

17:49.318 --> 17:51.972
He gave me this and called
it my end-of-year bonus.

17:52.007 --> 17:54.058
Cost me more to get it
appraised than it was worth.

17:54.089 --> 17:55.642
So why do you still have it?

17:55.677 --> 17:57.778
I don't know.

17:57.813 --> 17:59.847
[sighs]

17:59.882 --> 18:01.148
What are we doing here?

18:01.183 --> 18:02.382
Talking?

18:02.417 --> 18:04.771
No, on this ship

18:04.810 --> 18:07.154
with the crew of the "Raza."

18:07.189 --> 18:09.256
They're the galaxy's most wanted.

18:09.291 --> 18:11.091
Legends.

18:11.126 --> 18:13.727
- And we're useless.
- Speak for yourself.

18:13.762 --> 18:14.961
Because of us, they almost got killed

18:14.963 --> 18:16.163
on that Traugott colony,

18:16.198 --> 18:17.731
got trapped in a time loop,

18:17.766 --> 18:19.466
got sent off on a wild-goose chase...

18:19.501 --> 18:21.769
Uh, again, I need to point
out, that was all you.

18:21.804 --> 18:23.659
My point is, after
really thinking about it,

18:23.675 --> 18:25.405
it's become obvious:

18:25.440 --> 18:27.641
we don't belong here.

18:27.676 --> 18:30.010
I hate to say it, and I'm
sure they'll hate to hear it...

18:30.037 --> 18:31.524
I'm sure they'll be fine hearing it.

18:31.563 --> 18:33.113
[sighs]

18:33.148 --> 18:36.116
I'll let 'em know tonight at dinner.

18:36.151 --> 18:39.053
Hey, Adrian, we need
your help with something.

18:42.891 --> 18:45.226
On the other hand...

18:48.764 --> 18:50.864
<i>[tense music]</i>

18:50.899 --> 18:52.266
Got it?

18:52.301 --> 18:53.901
Yup.

18:57.210 --> 18:58.843
Beauties.

18:58.854 --> 19:00.154
[laughs]

19:00.190 --> 19:01.771
What do you say we find ourselves

19:01.795 --> 19:04.277
a nice fat, juicy target and
see what these babies can do?

19:04.279 --> 19:07.381
No. Priority number
one is finding a buyer.

19:07.416 --> 19:09.316
We'll keep one crate and sell the rest.

19:09.351 --> 19:11.318
- To who?
- There's a war going on.

19:11.353 --> 19:14.121
I'm sure there are plenty
of interested buyers.

19:14.156 --> 19:17.825
<i>Portia, we've received
a subspace transmission.</i>

19:17.860 --> 19:19.660
I told you to block
Ishida and Truffault.

19:19.695 --> 19:22.496
<i>It isn't Ishida or Truffault.</i>

19:24.099 --> 19:31.105
♪

19:32.349 --> 19:33.515
<i>Finally!</i>

19:33.518 --> 19:35.552
Adrian. Where's Tabor?

19:35.587 --> 19:37.754
<i>Oh, he's taken a leave of absence.</i>

19:37.789 --> 19:40.857
Ah, hiding under a rock
until the war blows over?

19:40.892 --> 19:43.326
<i>Probably, but that's not the point.</i>

19:43.361 --> 19:45.462
<i>Just because he's disappeared
doesn't mean you guys</i>

19:45.497 --> 19:48.098
<i>can go around violating your
contractual obligations.</i>

19:48.133 --> 19:50.900
Well, look who's stepping up.

19:50.935 --> 19:52.402
I didn't think you had it in you.

19:52.437 --> 19:54.337
I'm impressed.

19:54.372 --> 19:56.973
Wait, how did you get
this transmission channel?

19:57.008 --> 19:59.175
<i>Truffault called me.</i>

19:59.210 --> 20:01.644
- Of course.
<i>- Stealing an Ishida cruiser?</i>

20:01.679 --> 20:03.680
<i>Heisting a shipment of
cutting-edge missiles?</i>

20:03.715 --> 20:05.982
Ah, we saw an
opportunity, so we took it.

20:06.017 --> 20:06.937
<i>And it never occurred to you</i>

20:06.939 --> 20:08.550
<i>to give your representation a heads-up?</i>

20:08.581 --> 20:10.782
- Not really, no.
<i>- Not to mention the fact</i>

20:10.785 --> 20:13.156
<i>that you just screwed over the
only corporate friend you have.</i>

20:13.158 --> 20:15.091
Oh, we'll make new friends.

20:15.126 --> 20:17.694
And besides, Mikkei is
not going to do anything.

20:17.729 --> 20:18.946
They move against us,

20:18.949 --> 20:20.879
and they run the risk of
Ferrous Corp finding out

20:20.882 --> 20:23.004
they've been smuggling
missiles to Traugott.

20:23.007 --> 20:25.602
<i>Oh, well, okay. But you
should have dialed me in.</i>

20:25.637 --> 20:27.270
You mean Tabor, don't you?

20:27.305 --> 20:28.730
<i>Sure. Tabor and me.</i>

20:28.733 --> 20:29.849
<i>I mean, that's how this works, right?</i>

20:29.851 --> 20:32.347
- <i>You steal stuff. We sell it.</i>
- And take your cut.

20:32.350 --> 20:33.910
<i>It's the price of doing business.</i>

20:33.945 --> 20:35.378
Mm.

20:35.413 --> 20:37.447
So you think you can find a buyer

20:37.482 --> 20:39.282
for these missiles without Tabor?

20:39.317 --> 20:41.418
<i>- I already have one.</i>
- Who?

20:41.453 --> 20:43.787
<i>All you need to know is that
I'm getting you top price.</i>

20:47.358 --> 20:49.125
- I don't like it.
<i>- What's not to like?</i>

20:49.160 --> 20:50.322
<i>They get the missiles. We get the money.</i>

20:50.324 --> 20:52.064
- You vouch for this buyer?
<i>- Oh, completely.</i>

20:52.066 --> 20:53.830
Then I want you there for the exchange.

20:53.832 --> 20:56.667
<i>Well, that's... unusual.</i>

20:57.735 --> 21:02.072
Either you show up, or the deal is off.

21:02.107 --> 21:05.575
<i>Fine. I'll be there. Happy?</i>

21:05.610 --> 21:07.377
- Ambivalent.
<i>- Great.</i>

21:07.412 --> 21:11.115
<i>I'll send the coordinates once
I've made the arrangements.</i>

21:13.852 --> 21:16.086
Ooh, well, that went
better than expected.

21:16.121 --> 21:18.288
Yeah, congratulations.
You're a terrific liar.

21:18.323 --> 21:20.189
Hey, I was taking a chance
they would even know me.

21:20.191 --> 21:22.024
I already told you, in
the alternate universe,

21:22.026 --> 21:23.946
the crew of the "Raza"
never lost their memories.

21:23.962 --> 21:25.595
I know, but I was kinda thinking

21:25.630 --> 21:27.430
the alternate me might
be something different.

21:27.465 --> 21:28.531
Like what?

21:28.566 --> 21:29.666
Oh, I don't know.

21:29.701 --> 21:31.968
Concert pianist.

21:32.003 --> 21:33.536
[scoffs]

21:33.571 --> 21:35.305
My mom said I had a gift.

21:35.340 --> 21:37.007
Come on. We should get ready.

21:39.110 --> 21:42.579
I can do this, right?

21:45.083 --> 21:49.419
[whooshing]

21:49.454 --> 21:51.688
What if they suspect a setup?

21:51.723 --> 21:53.356
What if they make an example of me?

21:53.391 --> 21:54.957
Listen, you getting dead under my watch,

21:54.959 --> 21:56.392
that'll make me look really bad.

21:56.427 --> 21:57.794
I'm not gonna let that happen.

21:57.829 --> 22:00.196
Okay, that's... reassuring.

22:00.231 --> 22:01.965
Don't worry. All you got to do is talk,

22:02.000 --> 22:03.433
and we'll do the rest.

22:03.468 --> 22:04.868
Can I have the gun I was promised?

22:08.840 --> 22:10.006
Know how to use this thing?

22:10.041 --> 22:12.009
Pfft. Point and shoot?

22:13.411 --> 22:14.912
Lesson complete.

22:28.259 --> 22:29.593
<i>[device beeps]</i>

22:33.565 --> 22:35.031
Oh, uh, hi.

22:35.066 --> 22:37.934
Where's the buyer?

22:37.969 --> 22:40.870
Uh, g-guess he's running late.

22:40.905 --> 22:43.406
Uh, where's, uh, Portia?

22:43.441 --> 22:45.208
She's back on the
ship with the missiles.

22:45.243 --> 22:47.010
When the buyer shows
up, I'll radio to her,

22:47.045 --> 22:48.478
and she'll come down to meet us.

22:48.513 --> 22:50.580
Ah, well... well, that doesn't strike me

22:50.615 --> 22:53.116
as a particularly
efficient use of our time.

22:53.151 --> 22:56.252
We wait for the buyer.
Then we wait for Portia.

22:56.287 --> 22:57.287
See what I'm saying?

23:00.741 --> 23:02.425
Have... have you been
on the "Raza" long?

23:02.427 --> 23:03.793
'Cause I-I don't really
recognize your face.

23:03.795 --> 23:04.727
It's just...

23:04.738 --> 23:08.007
Don't! Don't.

23:08.066 --> 23:09.632
Don't what?

23:09.667 --> 23:11.734
You were going for your gun.

23:11.769 --> 23:13.970
No. I was adjusting my pants.

23:14.005 --> 23:16.573
No. You were definitely
going for your gun.

23:16.608 --> 23:19.642
No. This is me going for my gun.

23:19.677 --> 23:21.077
Stop. Don't! Don't move another muscle!

23:21.079 --> 23:22.087
I'm warning you!

23:22.090 --> 23:23.291
Drop it.

23:24.816 --> 23:27.283
The other Portia.

23:27.318 --> 23:29.519
I was hoping I'd get the
chance to see you again.

23:29.554 --> 23:31.548
You should be careful what you wish for.

23:31.551 --> 23:32.789
Now drop the weapon.

23:32.824 --> 23:34.724
Actually, I think you should drop yours.

23:34.759 --> 23:36.426
Oh? Why's that?

23:36.461 --> 23:37.434
Because if you don't,

23:37.437 --> 23:39.333
my team in the trees
will take you all out.

23:39.336 --> 23:42.665
You think I came down
here without backup?

23:42.700 --> 23:44.091
There's no one out there.

23:44.094 --> 23:46.728
Oh, why don't you test
me and see what happens?

23:46.773 --> 23:48.864
[grunts]

23:48.887 --> 23:50.306
[groaning]

23:50.341 --> 23:53.209
Ah! [grunts]

23:53.244 --> 23:55.278
God, in the... You know what?

23:55.313 --> 23:57.146
You are gonna regret that...

23:57.181 --> 23:59.282
right now!

23:59.317 --> 24:00.317
[bird shrieks]

24:03.855 --> 24:06.489
[bird shrieks]

24:06.524 --> 24:08.258
Right now!

24:08.293 --> 24:12.061
Guys, whenever you're ready!

24:12.064 --> 24:14.186
Ah, shit.

24:14.219 --> 24:15.852
Yeah, not so tough now, are you?

24:15.855 --> 24:17.633
Put that thing down
before you hurt someone.

24:17.635 --> 24:20.270
Oh, it's fine. Three
took the bullets out.

24:21.673 --> 24:23.540
Oh.

24:25.936 --> 24:29.779
<i>[ominous music]</i>

24:29.814 --> 24:34.284
[power whirring down]

24:34.319 --> 24:37.253
What the hell?

24:37.288 --> 24:38.321
[blaster fires]

24:38.356 --> 24:40.123
[grunts]

24:40.158 --> 24:44.994
<i>♪</i>

24:45.029 --> 24:46.562
I've secured the "Marauder."

24:46.597 --> 24:48.598
Moving on to phase two.

24:54.148 --> 24:55.883
Oh, it's hard to describe exactly,

24:55.883 --> 24:58.141
the feeling of having
a gun pointed at you.

24:58.164 --> 24:59.495
What a rush.

24:59.666 --> 25:02.190
It really puts life into perspective.

25:02.225 --> 25:04.325
I mean, just look at this sky.

25:04.360 --> 25:06.894
I've never seen it so blue and vibrant.

25:06.929 --> 25:08.863
Okay, can someone just
knock me unconscious

25:08.898 --> 25:10.264
and drag me the rest of the way?

25:10.299 --> 25:12.300
I cannot listen to any more of this.

25:12.335 --> 25:13.701
I've already killed you once.

25:13.736 --> 25:16.571
Please don't ask me to do it again.

25:16.606 --> 25:19.106
Wait, is that what happened
to the me in this reality?

25:19.141 --> 25:21.576
'Cause I looked him up. He
went missing a month ago.

25:21.611 --> 25:23.243
I figured he was just
keeping a low profile.

25:23.245 --> 25:24.712
Yeah, you think you're capable of that?

25:24.714 --> 25:25.547
Hell no.

25:25.550 --> 25:27.658
I mean, you killing me
makes a lot more sense.

25:27.661 --> 25:30.751
- How'd you do me?
- How did I do you?

25:30.786 --> 25:32.587
I spaced you.

25:32.622 --> 25:34.722
Damn. That's cold.

25:34.757 --> 25:36.224
Yeah, well, you double-crossed us,

25:36.259 --> 25:37.692
took my ship.

25:37.727 --> 25:39.994
I figured it was an
appropriate response.

25:40.029 --> 25:43.631
Plus, you spaced me first.

25:43.666 --> 25:46.000
You know, I can't help but
see this as an opportunity

25:46.035 --> 25:48.169
for a fresh start for both of us.

25:48.204 --> 25:49.424
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah, I mean,

25:49.427 --> 25:51.839
I'm a free agent, you
know, with a lot to offer

25:51.841 --> 25:55.009
both professionally and personally.

25:55.044 --> 25:58.713
You, um, looking for any new talent?

25:58.748 --> 26:00.915
[scoffs]

26:00.950 --> 26:02.884
No.

26:05.655 --> 26:08.959
<i>♪</i>

26:08.990 --> 26:10.590
Wait.

26:10.608 --> 26:12.494
This is where we parked the "Marauder."

26:14.956 --> 26:17.890
- Where's our shuttle?
- I got no idea.

26:17.933 --> 26:19.059
Taking it wasn't part of the plan.

26:19.061 --> 26:21.001
- No? What <i>was</i> the plan?
- Meet the buyer,

26:21.003 --> 26:22.570
steal the payments, keep the missiles.

26:22.605 --> 26:23.771
- Is that it?
- I don't know.

26:23.806 --> 26:25.339
Maybe kill Adrian and the buyer.

26:25.374 --> 26:27.175
There's always room for improvisation.

26:27.178 --> 26:30.745
But nobody said jack squat
about heisting your ride, though.

26:30.780 --> 26:32.213
Whew!

26:33.386 --> 26:35.416
You think if I had known
that getting captured

26:35.418 --> 26:37.538
was part of the plan, I
would have gone along with it?

26:39.388 --> 26:40.722
Move.

26:42.725 --> 26:46.594
<i>[tense music]</i>

26:46.629 --> 26:50.731
[whirring]

26:50.766 --> 26:52.900
<i>♪</i>

26:52.935 --> 26:55.270
You changed your clothes.

26:57.373 --> 26:58.673
Authentication sequence

26:58.708 --> 27:00.675
Three-Tango-Five-Gulf-Sierra-Six.

27:00.710 --> 27:03.878
Shutdown command.

27:03.913 --> 27:05.546
I'm sorry, Portia.

27:05.581 --> 27:07.549
That code is no longer valid.

27:10.786 --> 27:13.654
[grunting]

27:13.689 --> 27:20.227
<i>♪</i>

27:20.262 --> 27:22.330
[yelps]

27:22.365 --> 27:25.766
<i>♪</i>

27:25.801 --> 27:28.236
[blaster fires]

27:35.878 --> 27:39.313
[grunting]

27:39.348 --> 27:45.653
<i>♪</i>

27:45.688 --> 27:47.221
Aah! Ah.

27:47.256 --> 27:48.656
It's the other Portia.

27:48.691 --> 27:51.192
I know. She tried to deactivate me.

27:51.227 --> 27:53.294
- Where is she?
- Locked up.

27:53.329 --> 27:56.530
Good. Okay, I'm going
back down for the others.

27:56.565 --> 27:58.500
First I need to arm up.

28:00.002 --> 28:01.869
Under the circumstances,

28:01.904 --> 28:03.938
that's an excellent idea.

28:07.109 --> 28:08.776
There's a settlement west of here.

28:08.811 --> 28:10.711
They'll have surface-to-orbit
communication.

28:10.746 --> 28:12.713
We should contact the "Raza."

28:12.748 --> 28:14.815
That's four hours over rough terrain.

28:14.850 --> 28:16.817
Well, I can do it in two.

28:16.852 --> 28:18.386
Yes, I bet you could.

28:18.421 --> 28:19.920
But we're gonna stick together.

28:19.955 --> 28:21.525
Look, we knew there was a chance

28:21.528 --> 28:23.757
that this could happen,
but The Android is prepared.

28:23.759 --> 28:25.292
Our best bet is just to sit tight

28:25.327 --> 28:26.794
and let this play out.

28:26.829 --> 28:28.829
Wow, you <i>are</i> different.

28:28.864 --> 28:30.798
My Portia would be
beating the crap out of me

28:30.833 --> 28:33.702
right now for information.

28:33.741 --> 28:35.970
That was more of an
observation than a suggestion.

28:36.005 --> 28:39.306
Who else came over with
you on the "Marauder"?

28:39.341 --> 28:42.410
[laughs]

28:43.646 --> 28:45.045
Do I need to remind you

28:45.080 --> 28:47.282
that they used you and abandoned you?

28:49.185 --> 28:51.952
Okay. They used you and abandoned you.

28:51.987 --> 28:54.955
You're alone.

28:54.990 --> 28:56.486
- Everyone.
- What's that?

28:56.510 --> 28:58.292
We all hitched a ride when your "Raza"

28:58.294 --> 28:59.860
made the jump back to this reality:

28:59.895 --> 29:02.997
me, Portia, Boone, Tash, The Android.

29:03.032 --> 29:04.765
- What about Corso?
- Not so much.

29:04.800 --> 29:06.434
He's not really a team player.

29:06.469 --> 29:08.402
Right. Well, what have you and your team

29:08.437 --> 29:10.171
been up to since you came here?

29:10.206 --> 29:11.972
Taking it easy, seeing some sights.

29:12.007 --> 29:15.164
There's a lovely adults-only
botanical garden on Rigel-9.

29:15.195 --> 29:17.144
Also setting up this score.

29:17.179 --> 29:19.346
Right. Well, I'm sorry it
didn't work out for you.

29:19.381 --> 29:22.783
Oh, don't apologize.

29:22.818 --> 29:25.653
This is far from over.

29:25.700 --> 29:27.788
What the hell is going on up there?

29:27.823 --> 29:32.726
<i>♪</i>

29:32.761 --> 29:37.232
[rumbling]

29:39.947 --> 29:41.669
Any word from Portia?

29:41.704 --> 29:43.771
Not yet. Don't worry.

29:43.806 --> 29:45.506
It's all going according to plan.

29:45.541 --> 29:47.641
Is it? Shouldn't we
have heard back by now?

29:47.676 --> 29:50.544
Relax. We're prepared
for any complications.

29:50.579 --> 29:53.481
Besides, even if worse comes to worst,

29:53.516 --> 29:55.850
we still got one last card to play.

29:58.220 --> 29:59.820
[gasping]

29:59.855 --> 30:01.689
Right now, aboard that ship,

30:01.724 --> 30:04.091
your little friends, they're
in a whole world of trouble.

30:04.126 --> 30:05.159
Oh, yeah?

30:05.194 --> 30:06.494
Aah!

30:06.529 --> 30:07.728
You really think your Boone's

30:07.763 --> 30:09.196
gonna convince anyone he's me?

30:09.231 --> 30:10.865
- Fat chance.
- Little while back,

30:10.900 --> 30:12.566
you had me convinced you were him.

30:12.601 --> 30:14.361
Yeah, but that's 'cause
I'm a better actor.

30:14.370 --> 30:16.537
I do recall some performance issues.

30:16.572 --> 30:19.807
I bailed on you. There
was no performance.

30:19.842 --> 30:22.843
[laughs] Oh, I recall
that opening overture.

30:22.878 --> 30:24.211
You never had a chance

30:24.246 --> 30:25.779
to experience the crescendo, baby.

30:25.814 --> 30:27.448
That's because I was disappointed

30:27.483 --> 30:28.940
in your pianissimo.

30:28.971 --> 30:32.553
Okay, I think we've exhausted
the musical euphemisms.

30:32.588 --> 30:34.488
Can we go back to threatening
each other's lives?

30:34.490 --> 30:36.924
- Gladly.
- What?

30:36.959 --> 30:39.927
<i>[ominous music]</i>

30:39.962 --> 30:43.831
<i>♪</i>

30:43.866 --> 30:46.868
[door whirring]

30:48.704 --> 30:51.138
It would appear she's
waiting for something.

30:51.173 --> 30:52.373
Yeah?

30:52.408 --> 30:53.607
This.

30:53.642 --> 30:56.143
[blaster fires]

30:56.178 --> 30:58.746
<i>[tense music]</i>

30:58.781 --> 31:00.782
Bet you didn't see that coming.

31:04.052 --> 31:06.638
[door whirring and hissing]

31:08.831 --> 31:12.274
<i>- Hmm.</i>
- Boone?

31:12.309 --> 31:13.943
<i>I'd say "the one and
only," but lately,</i>

31:13.978 --> 31:16.445
<i>that doesn't seem to be the case.</i>

31:16.480 --> 31:18.180
What is going on?

31:18.215 --> 31:20.316
Seem to be locked out
of all the systems.

31:20.351 --> 31:22.785
Their Android must've installed
some kind of fail-safe.

31:22.788 --> 31:24.230
<i>I should be able to override it,</i>

31:24.233 --> 31:25.753
<i>but I'll need to do it on the bridge.</i>

31:25.753 --> 31:27.747
<i>Come down here and
open the door manually.</i>

31:27.750 --> 31:29.383
On my way.

31:29.386 --> 31:30.486
[door whirring]

31:30.489 --> 31:32.553
What the hell?

31:32.588 --> 31:34.188
Aah!

31:34.223 --> 31:36.490
Okay. Slight problem.

31:36.525 --> 31:38.592
<i>Ship seems to have a mind of its own.</i>

31:38.627 --> 31:40.027
What is that supposed to mean?

31:40.062 --> 31:42.329
Well, just...

31:42.332 --> 31:43.564
[exhales deeply]

31:43.567 --> 31:44.891
Just means it's gonna take me

31:44.894 --> 31:46.834
a little longer to
get there, that's all.

31:46.836 --> 31:48.769
Are you okay?

31:48.804 --> 31:51.305
Yeah.

31:51.340 --> 31:54.642
Aah! Ah.

31:54.677 --> 31:57.244
Whoa. Getting a little dizzy here.

31:57.279 --> 31:59.680
<i>Air seems to be a little bit light.</i>

31:59.715 --> 32:02.316
Activate the emergency
life-support systems right now.

32:02.351 --> 32:04.986
[breathing heavily]

32:08.657 --> 32:10.124
[groans]

32:10.159 --> 32:12.493
Actually, we did see it coming.

32:12.528 --> 32:14.329
[blaster fires]

32:19.468 --> 32:24.271
[whooshing]

32:24.306 --> 32:27.180
A ship just dropped out of FTL.

32:27.183 --> 32:28.750
It's the other "Raza."

32:28.753 --> 32:30.086
What took you so long?

32:30.089 --> 32:31.959
You were supposed to check in.

32:31.962 --> 32:34.467
<i>Sorry. I didn't realize you
were on a tight schedule.</i>

32:34.470 --> 32:35.603
Who the hell are you?

32:35.606 --> 32:36.576
<i>I'm the one holding</i>

32:36.579 --> 32:39.606
<i>two of your crew members...
Portia and Boone.</i>

32:39.609 --> 32:40.988
<i>You can call me Five.</i>

32:41.023 --> 32:42.740
Hey, kiddo!

32:42.743 --> 32:44.683
Three, is that you? Are you okay?

32:44.686 --> 32:46.260
Shut up.

32:46.287 --> 32:50.440
He's fine. But that could change.

32:50.487 --> 32:52.301
Then let's talk deal.

32:52.336 --> 32:55.471
I have two of yours,
and you have one of ours.

32:55.506 --> 32:57.507
I also have a stockpile of missiles

32:57.542 --> 33:00.676
waiting to go on a little test flight.

33:00.711 --> 33:02.044
You wouldn't dare open fire on us

33:02.046 --> 33:03.513
with your friends on board.

33:03.540 --> 33:05.257
Oh, "friends" is a pretty generous way

33:05.268 --> 33:08.084
of describing our relationship.

33:09.420 --> 33:11.888
<i>Destroy this ship, and you lose any hope</i>

33:11.923 --> 33:14.957
<i>of ever recovering the Blink Drive.</i>

33:14.992 --> 33:17.593
That's a good point.

33:17.628 --> 33:19.829
Guess I'll get over it.

33:19.864 --> 33:24.467
<i>♪</i>

33:24.502 --> 33:26.836
<i>[blaster fires]</i>

33:26.871 --> 33:28.205
[gasps]

33:30.968 --> 33:32.535
<i>I believe we can arrive</i>

33:32.538 --> 33:34.578
<i>at a mutually acceptable agreement.</i>

33:36.547 --> 33:38.415
Great!

33:59.270 --> 34:01.504
The missiles, the payment,
and your crew member

34:01.539 --> 34:03.139
have been deposited in a clearing

34:03.174 --> 34:06.609
1.42 kilometers northeast
of this location,

34:06.644 --> 34:07.710
as agreed upon.

34:07.745 --> 34:09.045
And your crew members

34:09.080 --> 34:10.400
have been deposited in a clearing

34:10.414 --> 34:13.382
1.63 kilometers southwest of here,

34:13.417 --> 34:14.817
as agreed upon.

34:14.851 --> 34:16.786
I'm afraid I had to restrain them.

34:16.821 --> 34:20.322
Oh, I restrained your
crew member as well.

34:20.358 --> 34:22.625
I also found it necessary to gag him.

34:22.659 --> 34:25.195
Understandable.

34:28.632 --> 34:31.434
By the way, it's pointless

34:31.469 --> 34:33.569
for your crew to come
after the Blink Drive.

34:33.603 --> 34:35.572
It's been damaged beyond repair.

34:37.275 --> 34:39.007
Are you being deceptive?

34:39.043 --> 34:41.277
No.

34:41.312 --> 34:44.813
In that case, I will
advise my crew of the fact

34:44.849 --> 34:47.550
and recommend we not pursue your ship.

34:47.585 --> 34:49.819
Are <i>you</i> being deceptive now?

34:49.853 --> 34:51.420
No.

34:51.455 --> 34:56.659
<i>♪</i>

34:56.694 --> 34:59.795
Commander, all the missiles

34:59.830 --> 35:02.164
and most of the cash accounted for.

35:02.199 --> 35:03.766
Most?

35:03.801 --> 35:05.635
Minus a modest service charge.

35:05.670 --> 35:07.036
We don't work for free.

35:07.071 --> 35:09.472
Thank you, Sergeant. That'll be all.

35:11.741 --> 35:13.442
It would have been
nice if you'd actually

35:13.444 --> 35:15.044
captured your impersonators.

35:15.079 --> 35:17.380
They could cause further
problems moving forward.

35:17.415 --> 35:19.348
Yes, I'm well aware of that.

35:19.383 --> 35:21.350
Tracking them down will
be our next priority.

35:21.385 --> 35:22.785
In the meantime, I'll have my office

35:22.787 --> 35:24.921
work up a new authentication protocol,

35:24.956 --> 35:26.949
- just for you.
- Thanks.

35:26.965 --> 35:28.925
Wait! Commander, don't leave.

35:30.328 --> 35:32.561
Is there something I
can do for you, Mr. Maro?

35:32.596 --> 35:35.865
I just need one little favor.

35:35.900 --> 35:37.967
You're gonna want to be
careful how you answer that.

35:37.969 --> 35:41.737
<i>♪</i>

35:41.772 --> 35:43.173
[sighs]

35:45.042 --> 35:47.276
So should I start packing?

35:47.311 --> 35:48.978
- You told them?
- No.

35:49.013 --> 35:50.679
I didn't think it was
right to get their hopes up.

35:50.681 --> 35:52.214
Too late for that.

35:52.249 --> 35:53.683
You guys taking a little trip?

35:53.718 --> 35:57.186
Yeah, we're off to Rasnov-4,

35:57.221 --> 35:58.621
courtesy of Commander Truffault.

35:58.656 --> 36:00.556
What's on Rasnov-4?

36:00.591 --> 36:02.124
My cousin.

36:02.159 --> 36:03.659
Plus, it's in Mikkei territory,

36:03.694 --> 36:05.962
so should be relatively
safe for a while.

36:05.997 --> 36:07.463
You guys have to understand,

36:07.498 --> 36:09.217
I do have other clients out there.

36:09.220 --> 36:12.067
As much as I'd love to, I can't just
be working with you exclusively.

36:12.069 --> 36:13.602
We'll try to hide our disappointment.

36:13.637 --> 36:16.739
Well, anyway, keep up the good work.

36:16.774 --> 36:18.475
Thank you.

36:19.643 --> 36:21.444
Try not to die.

36:21.479 --> 36:22.512
[chuckles]

36:23.681 --> 36:25.881
I guess I'll get my stuff.

36:25.916 --> 36:27.984
Just because he's leaving

36:28.019 --> 36:30.119
doesn't mean that you
have to leave as well.

36:30.154 --> 36:33.255
You could be a valuable
member of this crew.

36:33.290 --> 36:34.824
Three?

36:34.859 --> 36:37.360
Well, if she's gotta go, she's gotta go.

36:37.395 --> 36:38.861
He's right.

36:38.896 --> 36:40.930
Adrian paid me three months in advance.

36:40.965 --> 36:42.365
And let's face it: he wouldn't

36:42.400 --> 36:44.534
survive ten minutes without me, so...

36:47.171 --> 36:49.606
Take care of yourself.

36:53.377 --> 36:54.944
[sighs]

36:57.848 --> 36:59.615
Hey.

36:59.650 --> 37:01.917
Hey. Uh, I was just
about to come look for you

37:01.952 --> 37:03.619
to say good-bye.

37:03.654 --> 37:05.554
You sure about this?

37:05.589 --> 37:07.156
Yeah.

37:07.191 --> 37:09.458
Uh, as much as I
admire what you guys do,

37:09.493 --> 37:11.794
this isn't the life for me.

37:11.829 --> 37:14.530
Being down on that planet
pretty much confirmed that.

37:14.565 --> 37:16.932
We're all afraid.

37:16.967 --> 37:20.903
We just do a better job of hiding it.

37:20.938 --> 37:22.338
You're also pretty good

37:22.373 --> 37:24.173
at this whole action-adventure thing.

37:24.208 --> 37:26.942
I'm more of a
behind-the-scenes guy...

37:26.977 --> 37:29.378
You know, working the
angles, closing the deals.

37:29.413 --> 37:32.281
That's not you.

37:32.316 --> 37:34.116
Not the real you, anyway.

37:34.151 --> 37:37.653
Oh, yeah? What is the real me?

37:37.688 --> 37:42.525
Someone with a good heart
who tries way too hard.

37:44.495 --> 37:47.330
Someone I was just getting
used to having around.

37:49.600 --> 37:52.435
You know, you can come
with us if you want.

37:52.470 --> 37:54.603
Plenty of room at my cousin's place.

37:54.638 --> 37:56.972
Ride out the war in relative safety?

37:57.007 --> 37:58.908
[sighs]

37:58.943 --> 38:00.242
No, thanks.

38:00.277 --> 38:03.079
My place is here on this ship.

38:03.114 --> 38:06.082
Yeah, figured you'd say that.

38:06.117 --> 38:09.085
<i>[soft rock music]</i>

38:09.120 --> 38:14.390
<i>♪</i>

38:14.425 --> 38:16.693
See you around, Adrian.

38:18.362 --> 38:25.001
<i>♪</i>

38:25.970 --> 38:27.937
[exhales deeply]

38:31.175 --> 38:34.177
[whooshing]

38:42.953 --> 38:45.955
Guards to my location immediately.

38:45.990 --> 38:48.757
Signal's blocked.

38:48.792 --> 38:50.927
There's no need to turn
this into a bloodbath.

38:53.197 --> 38:55.064
Right,

38:55.099 --> 38:57.867
because we're such good friends,

38:57.902 --> 39:01.337
you decided to pop
by for a casual visit.

39:01.372 --> 39:02.905
You are not that far from the truth.

39:02.940 --> 39:04.473
You betrayed me.

39:04.508 --> 39:06.542
I can see why you would think that,

39:06.577 --> 39:08.344
but you're wrong,

39:08.379 --> 39:09.979
because I'm not who you think I am.

39:10.014 --> 39:12.748
Oh, so you're not Portia Lin?

39:12.783 --> 39:15.818
Mm, yes... and no.

39:17.521 --> 39:22.158
See, I'm here to tell you a story.

39:23.494 --> 39:25.027
And when I'm done,

39:25.062 --> 39:26.462
I'm confident you'll believe

39:26.497 --> 39:28.965
that we very much can be friends.

39:32.680 --> 39:37.149
It's high time we came
together to go after a...

39:37.174 --> 39:39.042
common enemy.

39:41.178 --> 39:44.180
Well, you, uh,

39:44.215 --> 39:46.282
have my attention.

39:53.284 --> 39:55.092
[gasps]

39:55.127 --> 39:58.061
<i>[ambient music]</i>

39:58.096 --> 40:04.168
<i>♪</i>

40:04.203 --> 40:06.236
[birds chirping]

40:06.271 --> 40:07.839
Sarah?

40:10.212 --> 40:11.278
Sarah.

40:11.313 --> 40:13.247
I'm here.

40:13.282 --> 40:15.783
[footsteps tapping]

40:15.818 --> 40:17.418
Hi.

40:17.453 --> 40:19.486
Hi.

40:19.521 --> 40:21.623
This is beautiful.

40:23.959 --> 40:25.492
I created it.

40:25.527 --> 40:28.131
How?

40:28.131 --> 40:29.898
Well, when this all started,

40:29.934 --> 40:33.869
everything around me was
like a... blank canvas.

40:33.904 --> 40:36.238
Hmm.

40:36.273 --> 40:39.975
But Five uploaded a program that...

40:40.010 --> 40:44.213
allows me to manipulate my environment,

40:44.248 --> 40:45.247
build things.

40:45.282 --> 40:46.849
[sniffs]

40:46.884 --> 40:50.119
She wanted me to make this my home.

40:50.154 --> 40:52.321
That kid, huh?

40:52.356 --> 40:53.522
[chuckles]

40:53.557 --> 40:54.990
First an empty room,

40:55.025 --> 40:58.127
and... now this.

40:58.162 --> 40:59.528
How long did all this take?

40:59.563 --> 41:01.375
I have no idea.

41:01.378 --> 41:03.239
I mean, I could stare at this flower,

41:03.267 --> 41:05.601
and maybe a few seconds pass,

41:05.636 --> 41:07.002
maybe a few hours.

41:07.037 --> 41:08.604
I can't tell the difference.

41:08.639 --> 41:09.739
Well, it's beautiful.

41:09.774 --> 41:11.408
Hmm.

41:16.313 --> 41:17.680
Did you make this too?

41:17.715 --> 41:19.915
- I've moved on to birds.
- Ah.

41:19.950 --> 41:23.452
But they're proving to
be a bit of a challenge.

41:23.487 --> 41:26.597
You're building yourself a
whole world here, aren't you?

41:26.634 --> 41:28.468
It's not just for me.

41:31.328 --> 41:33.429
I want you to be happy when you're here.

41:33.464 --> 41:35.464
I am.

41:35.499 --> 41:39.135
I want this to feel
like it's your home too.

41:39.170 --> 41:42.138
<i>[tender music]</i>

41:42.173 --> 41:44.106
<i>♪</i>

41:44.141 --> 41:45.841
[sighs]

41:45.876 --> 41:47.476
[moans softly]

41:47.511 --> 41:52.381
<i>♪</i>

41:52.416 --> 41:56.652
[whooshing]

41:56.687 --> 41:58.621
Where are we?

41:58.656 --> 42:00.816
I thought we were going to
a space station to resupply.

42:00.825 --> 42:02.391
Well, the Android told me

42:02.426 --> 42:04.393
that you haven't heard
from Six in a while.

42:04.428 --> 42:06.228
So we decided to resupply

42:06.263 --> 42:08.497
and check in on him at the same time.

42:08.532 --> 42:11.233
Really?

42:11.268 --> 42:13.702
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

42:13.737 --> 42:15.271
However, I haven't been able

42:15.306 --> 42:16.986
to establish communication
with the ground.

42:17.007 --> 42:18.394
Can you get a signal?

42:18.425 --> 42:20.776
No. There are no communication signals

42:20.811 --> 42:22.011
coming from the planet.

42:22.046 --> 42:23.345
Well, pull up a visual.

42:23.380 --> 42:25.514
Maybe their tower's been damaged.

42:25.549 --> 42:27.450
It... it looks fine to me.

42:27.485 --> 42:28.818
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

42:28.853 --> 42:31.020
Wait a minute. Magnify.

42:31.055 --> 42:35.825
<i>♪</i>

42:35.860 --> 42:37.260
Those are bodies.

42:38.496 --> 42:40.496
Oh, my God.

42:40.531 --> 42:41.698
Six!

42:42.337 --> 42:47.783
